 aus Dubai: Im kleinen afrikanischen Land Liberia spielt sich die grosse Klimapolitik ab</span></h2> <!----> <!----> <!----></div> <!----> <div class="metainfo metainfo--slide metainfo--longformvisual"><div class="metainfo__main metainfo__main--longformvisual"><!----> <div class="metainfo__wrapper"><span class="metainfo__item metainfo__item--author">Samuel Misteli (Text), Carmen Abd Ali (Bilder), River Cess County und Monrovia</span> <!----> <!----></div> <!----></div> <div class="metainfo__actions metainfo__actions--longformvisual "><!----> <!----> <!----></div></div> <!----></a> <!----></div></div> <!----></article><article data-source-element-widget="" class="teaser--article teaser--slide teaser--slide-mobile-fullscreen "><div id="id-ld_1763288" data-nzz-tid="teaser" data-nzz-cid="doc-1hbb7qqci0" data-nzz-cp="2" data-nzz-ct="Unsere Empfehlungen" data-nzz-pic="4" class="teaser teaser__layout--longformstandard teaser--size-slide teaser--slide-mobile-fullscreen"><!----> <!----> <!----> <!----> <div class="poster poster--slide poster--slide-longformstandard"><figure class="poster__figure poster__figure--image"><a href="/feuilleton/interview-dem-russischen-dissidenten-lew-ponomarjow-ld.1763288" data-nzz-referrer="teaserLink" class="teaser__link teaser__link--poster teaser__link--poster-slide"><div class="image-placeholder poster__placeholder"><img alt="Lew Ponomarjow ist überzeugt, dass Russlands Zukunft demokratisch ist. (Karin Hofer / NZZ)" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" loading="lazy" srcset="https://img.nzz.ch/2023/10/31/7763626c-6c6c-4aa0-a14d-24dfa0fe9799.jpeg?width=320&amp;height=427&amp;fit=bounds&amp;quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;crop=2607,3476,x747,y2025 320w, https://img.nzz.ch/2023/10/31/7763626c-6c6c-4aa0-a14d-24dfa0fe9799.jpeg?width=640&amp;height=853&amp;fit=bounds&amp;quality=75&amp;auto=webp&amp;crop=2607,3476,x747,y2025 640w, https://img.nzz.ch/2023/10/31/7763626c-6c6c-4aa0-a14d-24dfa0fe9799.jpeg?width